Meeting Held to Pay Highest Tribute to Kim Jong Suk  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hoeryong, December 20 (KCNA) -- A meeting of party members, servicepersons and youth was held in Hoeryong, North Hamgyong Province Thursday to pay highest tribute to anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk and vow loyalty to General Secretary Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the meeting were senior party, army and state officials, leading officials of the party and armed forces organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons of the Korean People's Army and officials, working people and youths and students in North Hamgyong Province and Hoeryong City. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket sent by Kim Jong Il was laid before the statue of Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Also placed before the statue were a floral basket in the joint name of the Central Committee and the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea and the National Defence Commission, the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly and the Cabinet of the DPRK and floral baskets in the name of KPA units and party and power organs, working people's organizations, institutions and enterprises, factories, farms and schools in North Hamgyong Province and Hoeryong City. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the meeting paid highest tribute to the statue of Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Choe Thae Bok, alternate member of the Political Bureau and secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, speaking on behalf of the WPK, said that Kim Jong Suk lives in the hearts of the Korean people as a lifeguard of President Kim Il Sung, outstanding political activist and mother of revolution for her great revolutionary career and the immortal revolutionary exploits she performed for the country, the revolution, the times and humankind and noble revolutionary trait, adding that the noble image of the woman commander of Mt. Paektu will shine long along with the history of Songun Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He called on all the people to uphold Kim Jong Il's Songun revolutionary leadership with loyalty despite whatever storm and stress and build without fail a great prosperous powerful socialist nation on this land true to the last instructions of the President and as desired by Kim Jong Suk during her lifetime and dynamically advance toward the final victory of the revolutionary cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 KPA Vice-Marshal Kim Il Chol, minister of the People's Armed Forces, speaking on behalf of the KPA, said that the special feat performed by Kim Jong Suk in the history of the nation was that she gave birth to and brought up the bright star of Mt. Paektu, giving a steady continuity to the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The officers and men of the People's Army will deeply trust and single-mindedly follow Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il only in whatever storm and stress and become ardent fighters and genuine Songun revolutionary comrades who would share their destiny with him to the end along the long journey of Songun revolution, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Yong Chol, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, speaking on behalf of the youth, said that the great revolutionary life of Kim Jong Suk was an admirable life totally dedicated to resolutely defending Kim Il Sung as she devoted everything to him, absolutely trusting and following him only and it was a noble life because she brought up young people with boundless loving care for the younger generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He declared that all the youths would learn from Kim Jong Suk's transparent revolutionary outlook on the leader and protect Kim Jong Il politico-ideologically and at the cost of their lives and become first-line death-defying corps and human bullets and bombs in the Songun era who would share their destiny with the headquarters of the revolution.

Senior Officials Visit Hoeryong 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hoeryong, December 20 (KCNA) -- Senior party, army and state officials, the chairman of a friendly party and leading officials of party and armed forces organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions visited the old home of Kim Jong Suk, an anti-Japanese war hero, in Hoeryong, North Hamgyong Province on Thursday on the occasion of her 90th birth anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Being told about stories of her childhood in the yard of the home, they looked round the historic relics preserved there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then they visited the Museum of Revolutionary Activities of Comrade Kim Jong Suk.

Kim Jong Suk's Birth Anniversary Commemorated  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- Working people and members of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea (GFTUK) met at the Central Workers' Hall Wednesday to commemorate the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Choe Su Dong, vice-chairman of the C.C., GFTUK, in a speech called on all the officials and members of the GFTUK to learn from the noble revolutionary outlook on the leader of Kim Jong Suk, who remained single-mindedly loyal to President Kim Il Sung after taking the road of the revolution in her early years, and become genuine revolutionary soldiers who firmly trust and follow Kim Jong Il only. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speaking next, anti-Japanese revolutionary fighter Ri Yong Suk recalled with deep emotion the historic facts that Kim Jong Suk gave birth and brought up the bright star of Mt. Paektu in the crucible of the anti-Japanese revolutionary war and devotedly defended Kim Il Sung like a fortress and shield. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those who had the honor of working under the care of Kim Jong Suk after the liberation of Korea spoke with deep emotion of what they felt about her noble traits. They recalled that Kim Jong Suk took deep care of the bereaved children of revolutionaries and showed warm loving care for them and trained workers into dependable builders of a rich and prosperous country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Put on the stage were mixed duet "We Live on Dashahe Hill," female trio of immortal classic masterpiece "My Mother," female solo "Arirang on Jiansanfeng," song to the accompaniment of Oungum "Lullaby on Jong Il Peak" and other numbers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A national students' oratorical meeting was held at Kim Chaek University of Technology on the same day to mark the same anniversary. The speakers spoke in high praises of the noble revolutionary career and exploits of Kim Jong Suk who rendered devoted services for the President, the country, the revolution and the people with transparent and revolutionary outlook on the leader, firm faith in sure victory and noble virtue. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A national poem and song presentation of school youth and children also took place in Hoeryong City on the same day to commemorate the 90th birth anniversary of Kim Jong Suk.

Art Performance Commemorates Kim Jong Suk's Birth Anniversary 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hoeryong, December 20 (KCNA) -- Art performance of the Korean People's Army Song and Dance Ensemble "The light of loyalty will remain long" was given here on Thursday to commemorate the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers put on the stage such pieces as female chorus "Kim Jong Suk Is Our Mother," male chorus "Mother Is Always with Red Flag" and dance "Azalea of Motherland" impressively depicting the undying revolutionary exploits of Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through mixed chorus "Glory to General Kim Jong Il," female solo "Thunder on Jong Il Peak" and other numbers, they well represented the rock-firm faith and will of the army and people of the DPRK to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche started in the forest of Mt. Paektu, true to the leadership of Kim Jong Il, brilliant commander of Songun. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was appreciated by senior party, army and state officials, the chairman of a friendly party, leading officials of party and armed forces' organs, working people's organizations, ministries and national institutions, servicepersons, and officials and working people in North Hamgyong Province and Hoeryong City.

Main Roadmap of Kim Jong Suk's Revolutionary Activities Made 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- The Geographical Institute under the State Academy of Sciences has newly made "Main Roadmap of Anti-Japanese Woman Hero Kim Jong Suk's Revolutionary Activities" (December 1917-September 1949). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The map is 223 cm in length and 143 cm in width centering Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, made in the form of wall map on her 90th birth anniversary, gives the main courses of her revolutionary activities in order of date. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The courses of the revolutionary activities she had conducted with the secret camp of Mt. Paektu as the center before and after February 16, Juche 31 (1942), the birthday of Kim Jong Il, are marked in detail in a larger-scale partial map. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The locations of the headquarters, venues of major meetings, secret camps, temporary secret bases, major battle sites and other places where she had conducted revolutionary activities during the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle are also marked on the map along with their dates. It therefore helps readers study her revolutionary activities in combination with the strategic and tactical intention of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Other larger-scale partial maps give the spots of her revolutionary activities in Pyongyang and Chongjin after the liberation of the country together with their dates. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The immortal feats performed by Kim Jong Suk are of weighty significance in accomplishing the revolutionary cause of Juche initiated by President Kim Il Sung.

Hoeryong City Spruced Up 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- An energetic work has been done this year to build better Hoeryong City, North Hamgyong Province where anti-Japanese woman hero Kim Jong Suk was born. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 More than ten objects including the dormitory of Kim Jong Suk Teacher Training College, the Hoeryong Koryo Medicine Factory and the Hoeryong Noodle Restaurant and dwellings for hundreds of families were newly built. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Multi-storied dwelling houses were designed and constructed along the Hoeryong Stream in semi-round, zigzag, terraced and straight shapes so as to afford better convenience in the people's life. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Many public buildings including the Hoeryong Hotel and the dwellings for thousands of households were repaired to suit the modern aesthetic taste. And roads were paved and footpaths laid out with color-blocks, which extend over 27,000 square meters altogether. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The infrastructure of the city was made perfect and the Hoeryong Stream was arranged well. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The local-industry factories in the city including the Hoeryong Lumber Processing Factory and the Hoeryong Essential Foodstuff Factory have made energetic efforts for general repair of buildings and technical updating of facilities so as to considerably raise the productive capacity and improve the quality of products. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 With the 90th birth anniversary of Kim Jong Suk at hand, the zeal of the officials and constructors is sky high and the looks of the city are changing day by day.

Congratulations to Kim Jong Il from Diplomatic Corps 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a floral basket and a congratulatory letter from the diplomatic corps here on the occasions of the 16th anniversary of his assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the new year Juche 97 (2008). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The basket and the letter were handed over to Foreign Minister Pak Ui Chun on Thursday by Egyptian Ambassador Moustafa Mohamed Ahmed Al Hatter who is doyen of the corps.

Floral Basket to Kim Jong Il from Palestine
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a basket of flowers from Chief of the Palestinian National Authority Mahmoud Abbas on the occasions of the 16th anniversary of his assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk and the new year Juche 97 (2008). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floral basket was conveyed to an official concerned by Palestinian Ambassador to the DPRK Mohammad Shahta Zarab on Thursday.

Gift to Kim Jong Il from Lao Delegation
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the visiting delegation of the Lao National Security Academy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The gift was conveyed to an official concerned on Thursday by Director of the academy Vilay Douangmany who is leading the delegation.

Floral Basket to Kim Jong Il from Chinese
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a floral basket from Zhou Wei, daughter of Zhou Baozhong who was a Chinese related to the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle, and her family on Thursday on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of his assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the basket were letters reading "We congratulate you General Kim Jong Il on the 16th anniversary of your assumption of the supreme commandership."

Chinese Pay Tribute to Kim Jong Suk
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- The family of Zhou Wei, daughter of Zhou Baozhong, Chinese related to the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle, sent a wreath on Thursday to be laid before the bust of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk in the Revolutionary Martyrs Cemetery on Mt. Taesong on the occasion of her 90th birth anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The wreath was placed before the bust on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Written on the ribbon of the wreath were letters reading "In commemoration of the 90th birth anniversary of Mother Kim Jong Suk."

Congratulations to Kim Jong Il from Japanese
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il received a basket of flowers and a gift from Takashi Nata, representative of Japan Ehime Institute for Modern Korean Studies, and a gift from Noboru Kameda, representative of the Society of the Japan-Korea Culture, on the occasions of the 16th anniversary of his assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The floral basket and gifts were conveyed to an official concerned on Thursday.

Military Attaches Corps Here Visits Cultural Exhibition
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- The military attaches corps here visited the Pyongyang Cultural Exhibition today on the occasion of the 16th anniversary of Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the corps looked around with deep attention photos and books showing the undying exploits of the peerlessly great persons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the end of the visit they made entries on the visitor's book.

Standard-Bearers of Songun Revolution Reared by Great Commander
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- With the approach of the 16th anniversary (December 24) of Kim Jong Il's taking the Supreme Commandership of the Korean People's Army, the Korean people are looking back on the exploits performed by him in training KPA soldiers into the standard-bearers and main force of the Songun revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He has made an endless journey of on-spot inspection to KPA units over the last four decades or more since he visited the Guard Seoul Ryu Kyong Su 105 Tank Division. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He put forth an army building program for modeling the whole army on the Juche idea and strengthened it into the army of the leader and the Party both in name and in reality. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He expounded the essence and requirements of the slogan "a-match-for-a hundred" set forth by President Kim Il Sung and ways for its realization, thus indicating a guideline for converting the KPA into an invincible army. He has also put his heart and soul into the modernization of its armaments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Having strengthened the KPA into a one-match-for-a hundred revolutionary army faithful to the Party's leadership, he placed deep trust in it as the main force for the accomplishment of the revolutionary cause of Juche after the mid-1990s when the revolution faced a grim test. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 And he formulated the fighting spirit displayed by soldiers in fulfilling the orders of the Supreme Commander as revolutionary soldier spirit and led the army to set examples in the van of socialist construction through a fuller display of the spirit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Under his leadership, they have successfully built large power stations, express highways and modern factories, carried out land rezoning and excavation of waterways and made a breakthrough in difficult and strained fields such as power industry, coal production and agriculture under the slogan "Let us take charge both of national defense and socialist construction!". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They set a pattern of a new socialist culture in the course of conducting brisk activities of company art performances vividly reflecting their militant and optimistic life with popular musical instruments, while sprucing up all buildings including barracks, mess halls and storehouses of subsidiary foodstuffs and operating their own bases of vegetable production and stockbreeding. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary soldier spirit, fighting morale and mode of life of the servicepersons have set the whole country aboil with revolutionary vigor and passion.

More Materials on U.S. Atrocities Displayed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Kaesong, December 19 (KCNA) -- More than 60 materials proving the atrocities committed by the U.S. imperialists against the Korean people for a long period were unearthed and displayed at the Kaesong City Hall for Working Class Education. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The staff of the above-said hall succeeded in discovering and collecting new documents and photos with the help of many persons who experienced or witnessed those brutalities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among those materials on display are photos telling about how U.S. imperialists built churches in the area of Kaesong and preached reactionary religious idea and worship towards America through missionaries under the mask of "philanthropist" in the first half of the last century and more than ten photos and evidence including tools and medicine bottle used for conducting tests on living bodies of innocent Koreans in hospitals under the signboard of "medical treatment." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new exhibits also include photos of GIs brutally killing many patriots and other people in the area of Kaesong who protested against the treacherous separate election forced upon them by the U.S. on May 10 after the liberation and hand writings of some persons who experienced the atrocities. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Visitors can see the materials testifying to the massacre of many patriots and other people committed by GIs in various places including Ryongjong-ri and Phungdok-ri and photos showing their destruction of the iron bridge across the River Ryesong and more than 10 tombs of kings dating back to the period of Koryo during the last Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 These facts clearly indicate that the U.S. imperialist aggressors are the worst man-killers and disturber of peace.

Moves of Japanese Right-Wing Reactionaries against DPRK Blasted 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- The evermore undisguised moves of the Japanese right-wing reactionaries come under fire by a signed article of Rodong Sinmun Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Noting that what is drawing particular attention in their moves is their vicious offensive against the DPRK, the article cites the following facts to prove it: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese Diet has recently decided to extend the sanctions against the DPRK including an embargo on DPRK-flagged ships six months under the pretext of the abduction issue. Timed to coincide with this, they are working hard to deter the United States from moving to delist the DPRK as a "sponsor of terrorism." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They have gone the lengths of warning the U.S. that its action to cross north Korea off the list of "sponsors of terrorism" would do harm to the Japan-U.S. alliance and push Japan to nuclear weaponization in the long-run. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their pressure offensive against the DPRK is nothing but a revelation of the wicked intention and uneasiness of those who are much upset by the might and invincibility of the DPRK's socialist system centering on the popular masses. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The points agreed upon at the six-party talks are in the process of implementation. Voices supporting this process are also heard from the social and academic circles of Japan. It is only the right-wing reactionaries and their henchmen that are opposed to it. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Those reactionaries are seized with extreme zeal for reinvasion as they are steeped in militarism and revanchism to the marrow of their bones. They are citing the non-existent DPRK's "nuclear and missile threat" as a pretext for justifying the moves stepped up by them to let Japan emerge a military giant and accelerate nuclear weaponization. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What should not be overlooked is that the above-mentioned offensive is aimed to render the Japanese politics reactionary and fascist and bar the relations between the DPRK and Japan from improving. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Their persistent reckless campaign against the DPRK would only precipitate their isolation and destruction. They had better stop such rash acts, urges the article.

Abrogation of NSL Urged in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- Victims of the "National Security Law" (NSL) and prisoners of conscience in south Korea reportedly held a meeting in Seoul on Dec. 16, demanding the repeal of the evil law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the meeting by Ri Jae Chun, who was sentenced to prison terms after being charged as a "wire-puller of the south Korean Federation of University Student Councils", Ku Son Ok, wife of Ri Jong Hun, a member of the Democratic Labor Party who has been detained owing to the case of the "Single-minded Association", and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They demanded that the NSL, a draconic law of the era, be abolished without fail for the reunification of Korea.

Kim Jong Suk Praised in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- A number of honorary titles, orders and medals were awarded to anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk and many books and poems praising her published and created in different countries during the last decade. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Tumbes City Council of Peru decided to present Kim Jong Suk, woman commander of Mt. Paektu, with the world honorary citizenship and the city's golden key on the occasion of her 80th birth anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Huaura Provincial Council of Peru adopted a decision to register her as an honorary citizen of Huacho City and presented her with a certificate of honorary citizen and a gold medal. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A special plenary meeting of the Loja City Government, the special Council of the Catamayo City Government of Loja Province, a special meeting of the Yantzaza City Council of Zamora Chinchipe Province and the Troncal City Council of Canar Province in Ecuador decided to award the titles of honorary citizen to her. And the French Institute for the Fidelity in Work conferred on her a gold medal and honorary certificate and the Cajamarca Provincial Council of Peru an honorary certificate of merit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A great king of a community in Aba City, Abia State of Nigeria awarded her the title of the chief of the tribe "Great mother of all people" and a souvenir key of Aba City proving that she is an honorary citizen of the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The League of Experts for Egyptian Cultural and International Civilization Dialogue granted her a cup depicting a man holding up the globe and a certificate praising her feats and the National Association of Writers and Artists of Peru the great medal "Sun of the National Association of Writers and Artists of Peru" and its certificate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "Contribution to Victory" Organizing Committee of the International Commemoration Movement of Russia conferred on her its social order "Contribution to Victory" together with its certificate and the written decision. The Nepal Journalist Association registered her as a special honorary member of the association. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Among the books and poems praising her were collection of true stories "Comrade Kim Jong Suk, an Indomitable Anti-Japanese Woman Fighter" and a picture album on her revolutionary activities brought out in China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Such books as "Flying towards the Sun", "Banner of Great Victory", "Mother of the Korean Revolution" and "Going through Storms" were published in Russia, Nepal, India, Peru and El Salvador. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  A Syrian political figure created epic "Kim Jong Suk, light of the sun" and a poet of Peru poem "Mother's Uniform".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There are also such poems as "Mother Kim Jong Suk, Azalea of Korea", "Poem Dedicated to Mother Kim Jong Suk", " Kim Jong Suk-Mother of Korea" and "Small Pocket-book of the Woman Commander" created by Zhou Wei, daughter of Zhou Baozhong who was a Chinese related to the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle, a Cuban poet, P.C. Sharma, chairman of the International Study Centre for Juche-Oriented Mass Media in Nepal, and other figures.

DPRK's Significant Days Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, December 20 (KCNA) -- A meeting was held in Russia, a ceremony of opening the Korean book, photo and handicraft exhibition in Mexico and a film show in Libya on Dec. 10 and 12 to commemorate the 16th anniversary of leader Kim Jong Il's assumption of office as supreme commander of the Korean People's Army and the 90th birth anniversary of anti-Japanese war hero Kim Jong Suk. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the functions were famous works of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il, photos showing the undying feats of their Songun revolutionary leadership, books and pictures introducing Songun Korea and handicrafts demonstrating the creative skills of the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made at the functions.

Kim Jong Il inspecciona compania adscrita a la Unidad 776 del EPC
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 20 de diciembre (ATCC) -- El Dirigente Kim Jong Il, Secretario General del Partido del Trabajo de Corea, Presidente del Comite de Defensa Nacional de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea y Comandante Supremo del Ejercito Popular de Corea, inspecciono una compania directamente subordinada a la Unidad No. 776 del EPC, laureada con el titulo del Septimo Regimiento de O Jung Hup. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Acompanaron al Dirigente los generales de ejercito del EPC, Hyon Chol Hae y Ri Myong Su. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ante todo, el Comandante Supremo averiguo como la compania cumple su mision y se cercioro del estado de estudio tecnico en el aula acondicionada para este fin. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Evaluo altamente los exitos logrados anteriormente por todos los choferes de la compania calificando de muy buena la conducta de ellos quienes cuidan sus camiones, que les significan armas de la revolucion, como si fueran sus pupilas y garantizan el transito sin accidentes al montar un excelente taller de reparacion y elevar constantemente la capacidad de conduccion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Enseno que los camioneros deben mejorar de continuo su nivel tecnico mediante la intensificacion del estudio tecnico para cumplir satisfactoriamente sus misiones de combate. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Tras indicar las tareas que se presentan ante la compania, atendio minuciosamente la vida de los uniformados recorriendo varios lugares como la sala de educacion, el dormitorio, el comedor, la cocina, el bano, el corral, etc. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Al ver los alimentos subsidiarios amontonados en el almacen para los productos de autoconsumo, elogio que ahora todas las unidades impulsan excelentemente la agricultura de autoabastecimiento dando panoramas peculiares nunca vistos antes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Este orgulloso exito deviene otro valioso producto de autososten que hicieron los militares del EPC en la epoca del Songun (priorizacion militar), destaco.   Encomio a la compania por haber registrado una innovacion colectiva en el mejoramiento de la vida material y cultural de los uniformados al acondicionar magnificas instalaciones culturales, educacionales y de intendencia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Ratifico que se debe prestar profunda atencion a la vida de los camioneros porque ellos trabajan mucho recorriendo casi todos los dias largas travesias.   El Comandante Supremo se fotografio junto a los uniformados de la subunidad.

Cuadros coreanos visitan casa natal de Kim Jong Suk en Hoeryong
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Hoeryong, 20 de diciembre (ATCC) -- En ocasion del 90o aniversario del natalicio (24 de diciembre) de la heroina de lucha antijaponesa Kim Jong Suk, los cuadros del partido, el ejercito y el Estado, el presidente de partido amigo, los funcionarios directivos de los organismos del partido y las fuerzas armadas, organizaciones de masas, ministerios y organos centrales visitaron este jueves su casa natal en Hoeryong de la provincia de Hamgyong del Norte. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Escuchando explicaciones sobre la infancia de Kim Jong Suk en el patio de esa casa historica, los visitantes pasaron revista a los objetos exhibidos en ella. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Luego, recorrieron el Museo de la Historia Revolucionaria de Kim Jong Suk.

Otorgados a Kim Jong Suk titulos honorificos en varios paises
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 20 de diciembre (ATCC) -- En los ultimos 10 anos, fueron otorgados a la heroina de lucha antijaponesa Kim Jong Suk titulos honorarios, ordenes y medallas de varios paises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Igualmente se crearon y se editaron numerosos libros y poesias en homenaje a ella. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@En ocasion del 80o aniversario de natalicio (24 de diciembre) de la generala del monte Paektu, el consejo de la ciudad de Tumbes del Peru decidio dedicarle el titulo de ciudadana honoraria del mundo y la llave de oro de la ciudad. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El consejo de la provincia peruana de Huaura le concedio el certificado de ciudadana honoraria de la ciudad de Huacho y la medalla de oro tras aprobar una resolucion correspondiente. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Quedaron aprobadas semejantes resoluciones en la reunion plenaria especial del gobierno de la ciudad de Loja, el consejo especial del gobierno de la Ciudad de Catamayo de la provincia de Loja, la reunion especial del consejo de la ciudad de Yantzaza de la provincia de Zamora Chinchipe, el Consejo de la Ciudad de Troncal de la provincia de Canar, del Ecuador. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Mientras tanto, el Instituto por la Fidelidad en Trabajo de Francia confirio la medalla de oro y el certificado honorario y el consejo de la provincia de Cajamarca del Peru, el diploma honorario. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El gran rey de una comunidad de la ciudad de Aba del Estado de Abia de Nigeria dedico a Kim Jong Suk el titulo de jefa de tribu "Gran madre de todo el pueblo" y la llave de la ciudad de Aba que la identifica como ciudadana honoraria de esta urbe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La Liga de los Expertos para el Dialogo de Civilizacion Cultural e Internacional de Egipto le dirigio el premio en que se ve un hombre sosteniendo la Tierra y el certificado de elogio a sus hazanas y la Asociacion Nacional de Escritores y Artistas del Peru, la gran medalla del "Sol de la Asociacion Nacional de Escritores y Artistas del Peru" y el diploma. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El Comite Organizador del Movimiento Conmemorativo Internacional de Rusia "Contribucion a la Victoria" le otorgo la orden social "Contribucion a la Victoria" junto con el certificado y resolucion y la Asociacion de Periodistas de Nepal la nombro como miembro especial de honor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Por otra parte, en China se dieron a luz la coleccion de historias autenticas "Camarada Kim Jong Suk, indoblegable combatiente de lucha antijaponesa" y el album alusivo a sus actividades revolucionarias. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
